1
00:00:05,055 --> 00:00:11,175
As Guru Mahārāj once told me,
“Analysis is a function of intellect.”

2
00:00:11,175 --> 00:00:15,115
[One Thing Known; Everything Known]

3
00:00:15,929 --> 00:00:21,644
Too much intellectualism creates doubt, 
doubt disturbs faith,

4
00:00:21,982 --> 00:00:26,136
and faith is our only way
to understand

5
00:00:26,136 --> 00:00:31,623
this plane, and the personalities
that populate that plane.

6
00:00:31,623 --> 00:00:34,324
This is what I want to say;

7
00:00:34,324 --> 00:00:42,558
that this should be at the basis
of everything that we undertake.

8
00:00:42,558 --> 00:00:45,873
A faithful position.

9
00:00:45,915 --> 00:00:50,328
‘Śraddhā’-śabde—viśvāsa kahe
sudṛḍha niśchaya

10
00:00:50,339 --> 00:00:55,285
kṛṣṇe bhakti kaile sarva-karma
kṛta haya (Cc: Madhya, 2.22.62):

11
00:00:55,405 --> 00:01:01,462
That, dedicating myself to the one,

12
00:01:01,462 --> 00:01:05,833
the many are understood.

13
00:01:05,876 --> 00:01:09,152
The One being Kṛsna.

14
00:01:09,188 --> 00:01:12,748
As Vedavyās announces
in the beginning of the Bhāgavatam,

15
00:01:12,748 --> 00:01:17,283
“Advaya-jñān”, 
‘One thing to be known.’

16
00:01:17,283 --> 00:01:21,990
Yasmin vijñāte sarvam evaṁ
vijñātaṁ bhavati (Mu: 1.3),

17
00:01:21,990 --> 00:01:25,996
the Upaniṣad śloka
that Guru Mahārāj so often quotes, saying,

18
00:01:25,996 --> 00:01:31,485
“Try to know that one thing,
upon knowing which, everything is known.”

19
00:01:31,485 --> 00:01:35,692
Try to acquire that one thing,
upon getting, everything is got.

20
00:01:35,692 --> 00:01:41,083
To satisfy that one person,
upon whom satisfying,

21
00:01:41,083 --> 00:01:48,025
everyone and everything is satisfied
in every way possible.

22
00:01:48,357 --> 00:01:54,788
Focused on the most exclusive plane,

23
00:01:54,788 --> 00:01:59,218
where the means of access
are all-inclusive.

